From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000031 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 02:15:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] mfd: twl-core: run clocks_init() only on twl4030

clocks_init() programs CFG_BOOT.HFCLK_FREQ + HIGH_PERF_SQ behind the
PM_MASTER protect key - a twl4030 procedure. On twl6030 the HFCLK rate
is strapped by the BOOT pins/OTP, the PM_MASTER offsets 0x05/0x0E
resolve to unrelated Phoenix PM registers, and no twl6030 DT wires an
"fck" clock - so every OMAP4 board just logs

  Skipping twl internal clock init and using bootloader value (unknown osc rate)

on every boot (the stock steelhead 3.0.8 kernel printed the same line).
Wiring an fck to silence it would be actively harmful: the writes would
blind-poke Phoenix PM state next to PHOENIX_DEV_ON. Gate the whole
procedure by class instead; the only CFG_BOOT consumer
(twl_get_hfclk_rate) serves the twl4030 USB PHY, which keeps working.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/drivers/mfd/twl-core.c
+++ b/drivers/mfd/twl-core.c
@@ -650,6 +650,19 @@
 	u32 rate;
 	u8 ctrl = HFCLK_FREQ_26_MHZ;
 
+	/*
+	 * CFG_BOOT.HFCLK_FREQ / HIGH_PERF_SQ programming is twl4030-only.
+	 * On twl6030 (Phoenix) the HFCLK rate comes from the BOOT pins/OTP,
+	 * and PM_MASTER+0x05 / +0x0E computed against TWL6030_BASEADD_PM_MASTER
+	 * are unrelated Phoenix PM registers (absolute 0x24/0x2D, next to
+	 * PHOENIX_DEV_ON) - writing the twl4030 key/ctrl values there would
+	 * be a blind poke at power-management state. There is nothing to
+	 * init on 6030 - and nothing to warn about ("Skipping twl internal
+	 * clock init..." fired on every OMAP4 boot).
+	 */
+	if (!twl_class_is_4030())
+		return;
+
 	osc = clk_get(dev, "fck");
 	if (IS_ERR(osc)) {
 		printk(KERN_WARNING "Skipping twl internal clock init and "
